WEBVTT

00:00.845 --> 00:03.050
Now you're gonna see me
fight for my child.

00:03.070 --> 00:05.121
You just messed with the wrong mother.

00:05.141 --> 00:06.693
<i>Previously on "Mistresses"...</i>

00:06.713 --> 00:09.028
- I'm Joss' ex.
- Ex?

00:09.226 --> 00:11.895
It's messy. This has
to be goodbye, right?

00:11.929 --> 00:14.964
Me and Sofia, we used to date.
There's nothing there anymore.

00:14.999 --> 00:16.566
It's purely professional.

00:16.600 --> 00:18.034
Lucy: Hey, Noel.

00:18.068 --> 00:19.903
I thought you weren't allowed
to hang around boys.

00:19.937 --> 00:21.008
I'm not.

00:21.028 --> 00:22.572
I'm not sure I'm so
good with this class.

00:22.606 --> 00:24.482
I'll go back to yoga and
Pilates just for you.

00:24.502 --> 00:25.508
Good.

00:25.543 --> 00:27.811
Don't leave me with him!

00:27.845 --> 00:29.913
[Gasps] [Grunting]

00:29.947 --> 00:31.681
[Screams]

00:31.715 --> 00:33.683
I suppose we should just
keep gambling, then, huh?

00:33.717 --> 00:36.186
- Sure.
- Come on.

00:36.220 --> 00:39.489
Let's go, baby. Give me something.

00:42.625 --> 00:45.428
Thank you for coming
on such short notice.

00:45.462 --> 00:49.732
I'm sure you understand
how serious this is.

00:50.318 --> 00:53.380
Um... what do you mean?
How serious what is?

00:55.034 --> 00:56.335
You're kidding, right?

00:56.369 --> 00:58.771
You're saying you know
nothing about the incident

00:58.805 --> 01:00.840
in the hotel hallway in Vegas

01:00.874 --> 01:03.342
between Joss and my nephew, Reza?

01:03.376 --> 01:04.709
I'm sorry, Jonathan.

01:04.744 --> 01:06.236
I-I have no idea
what you're talking about.

01:06.256 --> 01:08.207
There seems to have been an altercation.

01:08.227 --> 01:09.962
Reza was arguing with his girlfriend,

01:09.996 --> 01:14.962
and Joss misunderstood
what was going on, and...

01:14.982 --> 01:16.034
And?

01:16.069 --> 01:20.038
And in a misguided attempt
to protect the woman,

01:20.073 --> 01:22.104
Joss attacked Reza.

01:22.509 --> 01:23.882
Attacked?

01:24.278 --> 01:26.311
[Laughs] What do you mean "attacked"?

01:26.346 --> 01:27.980
She sent him to the hospital.

01:28.014 --> 01:30.870
He did his best to calm her
down and not to engage,

01:30.890 --> 01:33.318
but apparently, she was out of control.

01:33.353 --> 01:36.254
Okay. Wait a second.
Sorry. Um... [Chuckles]

01:36.289 --> 01:38.323
You're saying that
my fiancÃ©e and... and Reza

01:38.358 --> 01:40.859
got into a, what, like a fistfight?

01:42.528 --> 01:45.230
[Laughing] Oh, come on.
Jonathan, that is ridiculous.

01:45.264 --> 01:46.698
Yes, it is.

01:46.733 --> 01:48.500
And now I'm trying to figure out

01:48.534 --> 01:52.037
why one of my employees
left my favorite nephew

01:52.071 --> 01:54.539
bloody and bruised
with an injured elbow.

01:54.574 --> 01:57.009
Okay, there is no way
Joss would do that.

01:57.043 --> 01:58.710
I-It has to be a mistake.

01:58.745 --> 02:00.112
It isn't.

02:00.146 --> 02:02.180
And I don't appreciate the insinuation.

02:02.215 --> 02:04.683
So I suggest you speak to your fiancÃ©e

02:04.717 --> 02:06.685
before something else happens.

02:06.719 --> 02:10.088
- Are you threatening Joss?
- I'm not threatening anyone.

02:10.850 --> 02:13.759
I'm just saying that
this needs to get settled,

02:13.793 --> 02:16.261
one way or the other.

02:18.579 --> 02:22.434
Synced and corrected by johnyd13
~ www.addic7ed.com ~

02:22.468 --> 02:26.204
[Humming]

02:26.239 --> 02:28.473
Are you humming
the "Hamilton" soundtrack again?

02:28.508 --> 02:30.942
No, actually, I'm working
on my own thing.

02:30.977 --> 02:32.744
Sounds like "Hamilton" to me.

02:37.116 --> 02:38.417
Is that a...

02:38.451 --> 02:39.751
Condom.

02:39.786 --> 02:41.620
Seems like it.

02:44.397 --> 02:45.723
What? It's not mine.

02:45.743 --> 02:47.659
It fell out of Lucy's jacket!

02:47.693 --> 02:49.161
- Uh-oh.
- "Uh-oh"?

02:49.195 --> 02:51.163
That's all you have to say is "uh-oh"?

02:51.197 --> 02:53.565
There is gonna be a whole lot
more than "uh-oh" going on

02:53.599 --> 02:54.833
when I get my hands on her.

02:54.867 --> 02:57.102
- Whoa. Where you going?
- Pulling her out of school,

02:57.136 --> 02:59.738
and then I'm gonna beat
the crap out of that Noel kid.

02:59.772 --> 03:01.473
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Slow down.

03:01.507 --> 03:03.809
You're not going anywhere in this state.

03:03.843 --> 03:05.510
What do you mean?
The kid from her debate class?

03:05.545 --> 03:08.080
- That Noel?
- Yep. This just reeks of Noel.

03:08.114 --> 03:09.672
How do you even know
what Noel smells like?

03:09.692 --> 03:11.834
- Th-This is no time to joke!
- Okay, look. Here's an idea.

03:11.854 --> 03:13.318
How about we have him over for dinner?

03:13.352 --> 03:15.120
And that way, you know
what you're dealing with.

03:15.154 --> 03:16.718
You think he's just gonna
tell us if they're having sex?

03:16.738 --> 03:18.257
Give me 20 minutes
in the room with them,

03:18.277 --> 03:19.621
and I will be able to tell.

03:19.641 --> 03:22.128
I have a kind of radar
for this sort of thing.

03:23.445 --> 03:24.482
Fine.

03:24.516 --> 03:26.584
Okay. 20 minutes.

03:26.618 --> 03:30.221
That's all you get.
And after that, he is all mine.

03:30.255 --> 03:31.556
[Scoffs]

03:32.591 --> 03:34.425
Vivian's finally asleep.

03:34.459 --> 03:37.559
Our pediatrician just thinks
she has a little cold.

03:38.445 --> 03:40.264
Thanks for coming on such short notice.

03:40.299 --> 03:42.166
Of course. I'm just
glad you reached out.

03:42.201 --> 03:45.069
I wasn't sure
you'd be up for it after...

03:45.103 --> 03:46.915
[Chuckles] Oh, come on.

03:46.935 --> 03:48.578
Just because Savi's run off to Bali

03:48.598 --> 03:50.208
doesn't mean I'm gonna
leave you all alone

03:50.242 --> 03:52.726
to fight your deadbeat
baby daddy in court.

03:52.746 --> 03:56.126
And you really think we have
a shot at sole physical custody?

03:56.146 --> 03:58.223
I mean, most family courts
start out favoring the mother,

03:58.243 --> 04:00.578
and considering Alec
didn't even see Vivian

04:00.612 --> 04:03.280
for the first four months,
well, let's just say

04:03.315 --> 04:05.549
it's not exactly an advertisement
for good parenting.

04:05.584 --> 04:06.929
Does he even have a case?

04:06.949 --> 04:09.003
There's always a case to be made.

04:09.023 --> 04:10.725
But they probably know
they're not gonna get

04:10.745 --> 04:11.978
everything they ask for.

04:12.013 --> 04:13.647
All the decision-making power

04:13.681 --> 04:16.916
and restricting me to supervised
visits? I would hope so.

04:16.951 --> 04:18.791
My guess is that they're
asking for a lot upfront

04:18.812 --> 04:21.254
so they can look like they're
making big concessions later on.

04:21.289 --> 04:23.323
So you think we can resolve everything

04:23.357 --> 04:26.107
at the meeting today
without going to court?

04:26.794 --> 04:28.094
Hopefully.

04:28.129 --> 04:30.030
But I just want you to be prepared

04:30.064 --> 04:31.698
that this could get ugly.

04:31.732 --> 04:34.568
Now, is there anything
that Alec might use against you

04:34.602 --> 04:36.303
that I should know about?

04:36.663 --> 04:38.738
So, I guess you didn't read my book.

04:38.773 --> 04:40.740
Mm, no.

04:40.775 --> 04:42.876
[Sighs] Well, it's a little blunt

04:42.910 --> 04:45.378
about some of the mistakes I've made.

04:45.413 --> 04:48.582
But everything in it happened
long before I had Vivian.

04:48.616 --> 04:51.816
Yeah, well, they're gonna
use it as much as possible.

04:52.056 --> 04:54.054
- [Sighs]
- Look.

04:54.088 --> 04:58.425
This may be a long, nasty fight, Karen.

04:58.459 --> 05:01.528
You're willing to stick it out?

05:01.562 --> 05:04.664
To the bitter end. Whatever it takes.

05:08.060 --> 05:10.136
Ugh.

05:10.156 --> 05:12.906
Brian and his new girlfriend are
running a marathon together.

05:12.940 --> 05:15.308
Wow. That is a lot of neon.

05:15.343 --> 05:17.477
You dodged a bullet, honey.
A big, bright bullet.

05:17.511 --> 05:18.612
I know.

05:18.646 --> 05:21.846
It's just been so hard
to get Brian out of my system.

05:23.773 --> 05:25.886
You did this once...
Broke off an engagement.

05:25.920 --> 05:29.422
What was his name? Uh... Scott?

05:29.457 --> 05:30.657
Yeah.

05:30.691 --> 05:32.792
Definitely not my awesomest moment.

05:32.827 --> 05:37.230
I, uh... I stood him up at
our wedding for your brother.

05:37.265 --> 05:39.232
Last I heard, he was
getting married, though,

05:39.267 --> 05:40.934
so hopefully he's happy now.

05:40.968 --> 05:43.103
So, he's... He's a good guy?

05:43.137 --> 05:45.866
Mm-hmm. Nothing wrong with him at all?

05:46.376 --> 05:47.674
Nope.

05:47.708 --> 05:50.713
Although he did have a bit of
a kink for women's footwear.

05:50.733 --> 05:52.979
My frickin' arches killed me
the whole time we were dating.

05:53.014 --> 05:55.882
Joss. Do you have a second?

05:56.884 --> 05:58.800
I'll be, uh...

05:58.820 --> 06:01.922
Bye. [Clears throat] Good talk.

06:03.190 --> 06:04.691
So I guess you know.

06:04.725 --> 06:07.093
That you got into a fight with
Jonathan's nephew in Las Vegas?

06:07.128 --> 06:08.528
Yeah, he just told me.

06:08.562 --> 06:10.630
- Did you get hurt?
- No, I'm fine. Really.

06:10.665 --> 06:12.432
- When did this happen?
- Just...

06:12.466 --> 06:15.335
Okay. Do you remember
when I went upstairs

06:15.369 --> 06:18.038
to change clothes before we were
gonna leave to get married?

06:18.072 --> 06:19.706
There was this guy down the hall,

06:19.740 --> 06:21.975
and he was trying to get
this woman into his hotel room.

06:22.009 --> 06:24.344
- Like, what, against her will?
- It was crazy.

06:24.378 --> 06:26.313
I mean, he basically
slammed her against the wall,

06:26.347 --> 06:28.495
and then she screamed for help, and
when I went over there to stop him,

06:28.515 --> 06:29.983
that's when I realized that it was Reza.

06:30.017 --> 06:31.851
According to Jonathan,
you did more than just stop him.

06:31.886 --> 06:34.721
Y-You put him in the hospital.

06:34.755 --> 06:37.023
So, why... why didn't you
tell me any of this?

06:37.058 --> 06:39.859
I don't know. Maybe because I
knew that it would, you know,

06:39.894 --> 06:41.394
complicate things with you and Jonathan,

06:41.429 --> 06:43.196
and, honestly, I just wanted
it to go away, Harry.

06:43.230 --> 06:44.798
Well, that certainly hasn't happened

06:44.832 --> 06:46.866
and, you know, it would
have been nice to know

06:46.901 --> 06:48.868
before Jonathan called me
into his office, Joss.

06:48.903 --> 06:50.003
I felt like an idiot.

06:50.037 --> 06:51.465
I'm sorry.

06:52.846 --> 06:54.407
Is that what this is?

06:54.442 --> 06:56.009
From punching Reza?

06:56.043 --> 06:58.712
Not from some accident,
like you told me.

06:58.746 --> 06:59.879
Yeah.

06:59.914 --> 07:02.582
Okay. So... [Scoffs]

07:02.616 --> 07:04.918
You... You didn't trust me
enough to say anything.

07:04.952 --> 07:06.553
No, that's not true, Harry.

07:06.587 --> 07:08.254
It's just... It's not that simple.

07:08.289 --> 07:10.657
Well, it seems simple, Joss.
You just tell me.

07:10.691 --> 07:14.561
What doesn't seem simple is how you
were able to beat up Reza so easily.

07:14.595 --> 07:15.929
[Sighs]

07:15.963 --> 07:17.330
Okay.

07:17.365 --> 07:19.332
Um, I never stopped going
to my Impact class.

07:19.367 --> 07:22.569
So, y-you lied to me
about stopping the class,

07:22.603 --> 07:24.871
you lied to me about the fight,
then you lied to me

07:24.905 --> 07:26.583
about why you didn't want
to get married that night.

07:26.603 --> 07:29.761
Joss, is... is there
anything you haven't
been lying to me about?

07:29.781 --> 07:31.444
- Harry...
- What is going on with you, Joss?

07:31.479 --> 07:32.445
Nothing is going on with me!

07:32.480 --> 07:35.254
I... I saw something,
and I reacted. I'm sorry.

07:35.274 --> 07:37.050
Well, that's great,
but I still have to figure out

07:37.084 --> 07:38.618
what I'm supposed to tell Jonathan,

07:38.652 --> 07:41.260
especially since he thinks
you attacked Reza unprovoked.

07:41.280 --> 07:43.523
Well, maybe try telling him
the truth, Harry.

07:43.557 --> 07:46.292
âª

07:49.296 --> 07:51.364
In addition, Faith is a pediatrician

07:51.399 --> 07:53.800
who plans to become
a full-time caregiver.

07:53.834 --> 07:55.969
That role in Karen's home
has already been filled

07:56.003 --> 07:58.071
by an endless rotation of nannies.

07:58.105 --> 08:00.907
Well, I imagine
a second caretaker was helpful

08:00.941 --> 08:02.706
after Vivian's father abandoned her.

08:02.726 --> 08:05.292
I only stayed away
because Karen asked me to

08:05.312 --> 08:06.946
and I wanted to respect her wishes.

08:06.980 --> 08:08.081
That's a lie.

08:08.115 --> 08:11.739
You chose to miss the first
four months of her life.

08:11.759 --> 08:13.437
You don't know the first
thing about Vivian.

08:13.457 --> 08:14.964
How dare you come here now

08:14.984 --> 08:17.051
and try to take her away from me.

08:18.692 --> 08:21.094
Vivian has just begun the most important

08:21.128 --> 08:23.229
developmental years of her life.

08:23.263 --> 08:24.997
It is vital that she be
in an environment

08:25.032 --> 08:28.404
where she will receive maximum
intellectual stimulation.

08:28.424 --> 08:29.435
What the hell is that?

08:29.470 --> 08:32.972
Look, I think we all want to
reach some kind of compromise

08:33.006 --> 08:35.741
so we can avoid a lengthy court process.

08:35.775 --> 08:37.844
I have no interest in compromising.

08:37.878 --> 08:39.846
You have no proof that Karen has been

08:39.880 --> 08:42.115
anything other than a perfect mother.

08:42.149 --> 08:44.751
Actually, I didn't want
to bring this up,

08:44.785 --> 08:46.686
but I assume you remember calling me

08:46.720 --> 08:48.650
when I was in Costa Rica?

08:48.670 --> 08:49.689
Calling you?

08:49.723 --> 08:51.157
When you were 12 weeks pregnant

08:51.191 --> 08:53.923
on the way to the doctor
to discuss an abortion?

08:55.696 --> 08:58.733
I'm not sure what
that has to do with this.

08:58.753 --> 09:00.133
I still have the voicemails,

09:00.153 --> 09:02.869
and they don't sugarcoat the fact
that you didn't want this baby

09:02.903 --> 09:04.305
and you never did.

09:04.325 --> 09:06.628
Obviously I didn't go through with it.

09:06.648 --> 09:08.174
And it's not like you begged me not to.

09:08.208 --> 09:10.209
I was in no position to ask you

09:10.244 --> 09:12.945
to keep a baby you didn't want.

09:12.980 --> 09:15.782
We're not giving up until we get
full custody of Vivian.

09:15.816 --> 09:18.785
If you want a fight, we're ready.

09:18.819 --> 09:21.287
âª

09:28.666 --> 09:30.141
I need your advice.

09:30.161 --> 09:32.963
But you have to promise that you
won't say anything to anyone.

09:32.997 --> 09:34.965
Okay.

09:34.999 --> 09:36.533
I met someone.

09:36.567 --> 09:37.601
That's great!

09:37.635 --> 09:40.837
Well [Sighs] not so fast.

09:40.872 --> 09:42.039
It's Scott.

09:42.073 --> 09:43.840
Scott Bakula?

09:43.875 --> 09:45.976
Scott Trosman.

09:46.010 --> 09:49.980
As in Dr. Scott Trosman,
Joss' ex-fiancÃ©?

09:50.618 --> 09:52.983
Oh, no, no, no.

09:53.017 --> 09:54.551
When we realized the Joss connection,

09:54.585 --> 09:56.286
- we broke things off.
- Good.

09:56.320 --> 09:57.888
Now I'm thinking that was a mistake.

09:57.922 --> 09:59.523
You're thinking that was a mistake?

09:59.557 --> 10:02.893
If Joss ever finds out... wow.

10:02.927 --> 10:04.528
So you think she would be mad?

10:04.562 --> 10:06.897
Like, how mad on a scale from 1 to 10?

10:06.931 --> 10:08.665
10 isn't high enough.

10:08.699 --> 10:10.500
And that's not even factoring in Harry,

10:10.535 --> 10:11.802
who would be at least a 20.

10:11.836 --> 10:14.471
Seriously, of all the people
in Los Angeles?

10:14.505 --> 10:16.173
You can't choose who you fall for.

10:16.207 --> 10:19.009
Aren't you the one dating your
dead husband's mistress' brother?

10:19.043 --> 10:21.078
We're not talking about me right now.

10:21.112 --> 10:22.679
Is it really worth it?

10:22.713 --> 10:26.216
Pissing off your brother and Joss
for a hot guy you barely even know?

10:26.250 --> 10:27.417
[Bell jingles]

10:27.452 --> 10:29.134
But I do know him.

10:29.154 --> 10:31.644
And it's not just physical.
We have a real connection.

10:31.664 --> 10:34.691
I haven't felt this way
since I first met Brian.

10:34.725 --> 10:36.359
And I know Joss wants him to be happy,

10:36.394 --> 10:38.411
so why not give it a try?

10:38.431 --> 10:39.996
I just think it's a messy situation,

10:40.031 --> 10:41.531
and maybe you should just let it lie.

10:41.566 --> 10:43.567
- Well, I don't agree!
- I thought you wanted my advice.

10:43.601 --> 10:46.134
Not if I don't agree with it.

10:46.416 --> 10:49.106
You know what?
You can do whatever you want.

10:49.140 --> 10:51.875
But please leave me out of it.

10:55.379 --> 10:57.380
How could you do this?

10:57.415 --> 11:00.750
You took my most vulnerable
moment and used it against me.

11:00.785 --> 11:04.020
I'm sorry, but you said you were
unwilling to compromise,

11:04.055 --> 11:05.889
and I have to do
what's best for our daughter.

11:05.923 --> 11:08.725
- Don't you dare hide behind Vivian.
- I'm not.

11:08.759 --> 11:12.796
I genuinely think the best place
for Vivian is with Faith and I.

11:12.830 --> 11:15.432
But her well-being
is the most important thing.

11:15.466 --> 11:17.134
Do you really believe that,

11:17.168 --> 11:19.436
or is this just
your way of punishing me?

11:19.470 --> 11:20.705
- Punishing you for what?
- I think

11:20.725 --> 11:22.572
you blame me for Vivian's death.

11:22.607 --> 11:25.308
I think you're bitter
that you had to share

11:25.343 --> 11:27.711
the last year of her life with me,

11:27.745 --> 11:31.114
and I think that resentment
is clouding your judgment.

11:31.149 --> 11:33.950
I care about you, and I always will.

11:33.985 --> 11:36.786
- Please.
- I'm here to let you off the hook.

11:36.821 --> 11:39.956
Just sign the papers and you don't
have to deal with any of this.

11:39.991 --> 11:42.692
You know it's best for all of us.

11:44.028 --> 11:46.561
I guess I'll see you in court. [Sighs]

11:46.940 --> 11:48.431
[Sighs]

11:49.403 --> 11:50.881
Are you okay? You didn't get hurt?

11:50.901 --> 11:52.269
I promise I'm fine.

11:52.303 --> 11:55.505
It's... It's actually Harry
that has the problem.

11:55.540 --> 11:56.773
Why? What's wrong with Harry?

11:56.807 --> 11:59.664
Ugh. He's pissed that I didn't
tell him about what happened.

11:59.684 --> 12:01.433
And I lied to him about a few things.

12:01.453 --> 12:03.483
You didn't think he would understand?

12:03.503 --> 12:06.238
No, I just, you know, I knew
it would turn into a big deal.

12:06.272 --> 12:08.807
It was Jonathan's nephew,
so it would affect his business,

12:08.842 --> 12:10.642
and then he'd want to know
how I beat the guy up,

12:10.677 --> 12:12.778
and I'd have to explain
that I never quit Impact,

12:12.812 --> 12:14.479
even though I told him that I did.

12:15.682 --> 12:18.483
So, you've basically
been lying to my brother

12:18.518 --> 12:19.785
about everything.

12:19.819 --> 12:22.087
W... Uh, not everything.

12:22.121 --> 12:24.256
Sometimes people feel like
they have to lie

12:24.290 --> 12:26.291
because the truth
is too hard to explain.

12:26.997 --> 12:28.059
Exactly.

12:28.079 --> 12:30.963
Okay, can we just please change
the subject now? Anything else.

12:30.997 --> 12:33.265
